# 📄 Development Rules and Guidelines

## Overview

This documentation contains comprehensive development guidelines and best practices for our TanStack Start application. The documentation is organized using a domain-driven hierarchy, making it easy to find relevant information for specific needs.

## Directory Structure

```sh
domains/
├── core/               # Core principles and standards
│   ├── principles.mdc  # Fundamental development principles
│   ├── architecture.mdc# System design and patterns
│   └── standards.mdc   # Code quality and style
├── frontend/          # Frontend-specific rules
│   ├── react/        # React patterns and practices
│   ├── typescript.mdc # TypeScript guidelines
│   └── testing.mdc   # Frontend testing
└── tanstack/         # TanStack-specific guidelines
    ├── start/        # Start framework guidelines
    ├── query/        # Query patterns
    └── router/       # Routing patterns

processes/
├── consistency/      # Consistency guidelines
├── maintenance/      # Maintenance procedures
├── migration/        # Migration guides
└── decision-making/  # Decision processes
```

